This paper deals with argumentation datasets and computational methods for analyzing argumentative text, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses user traits and their effect on the debate outcome, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the dataset presented in the paper could be relevant to researchers working on data mining and machine learning, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
